annotations.description: Unstructured key value map that may be set by external tools to store and arbitrary metadata. They are not queryable and should be preserved when modifying objects. **Note**: This field is non-authoritative, and will only manage the annotations present in your configuration. Please refer to the field 'effective_annotations' for all of the annotations present on the resource.

backend.description: The ID of the Backend that this Build applies to

build_id.description: The user-specified ID of the build being created.

build_logs_uri.description: The location of the [Cloud Build logs](https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/view-build-results) for the build process.

create_time.description: Time at which the build was created.

effective_annotations.description: All of annotations (key/value pairs) present on the resource in GCP, including the annotations configured through Terraform, other clients and services.

effective_labels.description: All of labels (key/value pairs) present on the resource in GCP, including the labels configured through Terraform, other clients and services.

environment.description: The environment name of the backend when this build was created.

error.description: The 'Status' type defines a logical error model that is suitable for different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs. It is used by [gRPC](https://github.com/grpc). Each 'Status' message contains three pieces of data: error code, error message, and error details. You can find out more about this error model and how to work with it in the [API Design Guide](https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/errors).

error_source.description: The source of the error for the build, if in a 'FAILED' state. Possible values: CLOUD_BUILD CLOUD_RUN

etag.description: Server-computed checksum based on other values; may be sent on update or delete to ensure operation is done on expected resource.

image.description: The Artifact Registry [container image](https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.dockerImages) URI, used by the Cloud Run ['revision'](https://cloud.google.com/run/docs/reference/rest/v2/projects.locations.services.revisions) for this build.

labels.description: Unstructured key value map that can be used to organize and categorize objects. **Note**: This field is non-authoritative, and will only manage the labels present in your configuration. Please refer to the field 'effective_labels' for all of the labels present on the resource.

location.description: The location of the Backend that this Build applies to

name.description: Identifier. The resource name of the build. Format: 'projects/{project}/locations/{locationId}/backends/{backendId}/builds/{buildId}'.

state.description: The state of the build. Possible values: BUILDING BUILT DEPLOYING READY FAILED

terraform_labels.description: The combination of labels configured directly on the resource and default labels configured on the provider.

update_time.description: Time at which the build was last updated.

author.description: Version control metadata for a user associated with a resolved codebase. Currently assumes a Git user.

branch.description: The branch in the codebase to build from, using the latest commit.

commit.description: The commit in the codebase to build from.

commit_message.description: The message of a codebase change.

commit_time.description: The time the change was made.

display_name.description: The human-friendly name to use for this Codebase when displaying a build. We use the first eight characters of the SHA-1 hash for GitHub.com.

hash.description: The full SHA-1 hash of a Git commit, if available.

uri.description: A URI linking to the codebase on an hosting provider's website. May not be valid if the commit has been rebased or force-pushed out of existence in the linked repository.

block.description: A codebase source, representing the state of the codebase that the build will be created at.

image.description: A URI representing a container for the backend to use.

block.description: The URI of an Artifact Registry [container image](https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.dockerImages) to use as the build source.
